# FORMAT :
#
# VAR CATEGORIES Brief Description
# Followed by nothing or
# =OPTIONAL|LINE|FOR|POSSIBLE|VALUES|IF|REQUIRED
# or
# $DIRECTORY/filespec_?.so
# where the ? would be the setting (like $AUBITDIR/lib/libSQL_?.so for SQLTYPE)
#
# The last portion is indented with a 'TAB' and gives a fuller description..
#
# AUBIT_Y2K RUNTIME Specify Y2K handling of dates
# <tab>+n (n<100) - set to nearest year using +n years from today as limit for future
#  "   -n (n>-100) - set to nearest year using -n from today as limit for past
#  "   (note: -25 = +75 )
#  "   eg if year=1997
#  "   n=20   > 17 will be taken as historic anything <17 is future
#  "   n=-20  <77 will be taken as future >77 is in the past
#  "   XX00 - always use century XX
#  "   999  - Do not add anything - dealing with AD 0-99
#  "   -999 - use current century
#
A4GL_AUTOBANG UI/TUI  Enable automatic ! for command entry
=YES|NO
	(like dbaccess menus) for all applicable statements
A4GL_CINT COMPILE/RUNTIME Full path to CINT C-code interpreter, if installed, othewise 'no'. Used by 4glc compiler to run C compiled code after compilation.
A4GL_C_COMP COMPILE Name of the executable of C compiler to use
A4GL_EXE_EXT COMPILE Extension to use for executable files compiled by Aubit compiler
A4GL_FORMTYPE FORMS/RUNTIME Determine which runtime library to use for reading forms
A4GL_FRM_BASE_EXT RUNTIME/COMPILE/FORMS Default form extension (for all packing types)
A4GL_HELPTYPE RUNTIME Determin which runtime library to use for displaying help messages
A4GL_HLP_EXT RUNTIME/COMPILE Specify the default extension for a help file
A4GL_INIFILE COMPILE/RUNTIME Environment variable optionaly specifiying aubitrc file to use
A4GL_LEXDIALECT COMPILE/RUNTIME Determine which ESQL/C dialect to use
A4GL_LEXTYPE COMPILE Determine what language to convert the 4GL code into
A4GL_LIB_EXT COMPILE Extension to use for libraries created by Aubit compiler
A4GL_LINK_LIBS COMPILE Libraries to link against when producing executables
A4GL_MENUTYPE COMPILE/RUNTIME Determine library to use for menuhandlers (not normal 4GL menus)
A4GL_MNU_BASE_EXT COMPILE/RUNTIME Base extension (without packer extension) to use when compiling/opening menu files
A4GL_MSGTYPE RUNTIME Determine library for help message handling
A4GL_MV_CMD COMPILE Command to ise to move files on the file system
A4GL_OBJ_EXT COMPILE extension to use when compiling 4GL modules to objects
A4GL_OMIT_NO_LOG
A4GL_PACKED_EXT COMPILE/RUNTIME Determine file extension for packing
A4GL_PACKER COMPILE/RUNTIME Determine library for packing forms/menus etc
$AUBITDIR/libPACKER_?.so
A4GL_PDFTYPE RUNTIME Determine which library to use for extended reports
A4GL_RESERVEWORDS COMPILE --obsolete?-- used to determine if traditionaly reserved words in 4GL language should be treated as reserverd
A4GL_RM_CMD COMPILE Command to use for deleting files on the file system
A4GL_SAPDB_ESQLC COMPILE Full path to SAP DB ESQL/C compiler executable used when compiling EC output for SAP DB
A4GL_SQLTYPE RUNTIME/COMPILE Determine which library to use to connect to the database
A4GL_UI RUNTIME Determine which library to use for the user interface
A4GL_USE_ALIAS_AS
=YES|NO
A4GL_XML_EXT COMPILE/RUNTIME extension to use when creating output (forms,menus) using XML packer

ALWAYSCLOBBER
=YES|NO
ANSI_ERROR When ANSI_ERROR is set to Yes, compiler will abort id non ANSI SQL 92 statemt is found in source code. If neither of these is set no checking is performed.
ANSI_WARN COMPILE ANSI SQL 92 checking mode: When ANSI_WARN is set to Yes compiler will display a warning if it encounters static SQL statement not confitming to ANSI SQL 92 specification
ARR_DIR_MSG UI/TUI Display/Input array message 'There are no more rows in that direction'

AUBITDIR COMPILE/RUNTIME Specify the location of the aubit source tree
AUBITETC COMPILE/RUNTIME This internal variable points to default location of Aubit config files Default: /etc/opt/aubit4gl You should not need to change this.
AUBIT_Y2K RUNTIME Specify Y2K handling of dates
	+n (n<100) - set to nearest year using +n years from today as limit for future
	-n (n>-100) - set to nearest year using -n from today as limit for past
	(note: -25 = +75 )
	eg if year=1997
	n=20   > 17 will be taken as historic anything <17 is future
	n=-20  <77 will be taken as future >77 is in the past 
	XX00 - always use century XX
	999  - Do not add anything - dealing with AD 0-99
	-999 - use current century
AUTONULL COMPILE Auto initializing module and function local variables. Numeric variables are initializet to 0, everything else to NULL To turn on, set to 'Y' (??? or is that YES ???)
=YES|NO
BACKGROUND UI/TUI Default background character (in hex) when creating a window
	(eg 2E for a '.')


